Use Case 1\
Description\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs24 \cf0 This use case describes how a user connects to the citrix server while using our gps validation software\

\b\fs28 Actors\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa300\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf0  1) Travelling Professor\
 2) Citrix server\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\ql\qnatural

\fs28 \cf0  Preconditions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs24 \cf0 The professors computer is outfitted with a working GPS module.
\f1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 
\f0 The professor's computer is able to connect to the internet.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\ql\qnatural

\b\fs28 \cf0  Basic Flow of Events\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs24 \cf0 1. Professor tries to use Citrix.\
2. The system prompts the professor to log in\
3. login credentials are verified\
4. The GPS module checks the professor's current location\
5. This GPS co-ordinate data is checked against a remote database of valid geolocations\
6. The system verifies that the co-ordinate is acceptable.\
7. The user is logged into the system\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\ql\qnatural

\b\fs28 \cf0  Alternative Flows
\b0 \
1) Invalid login\
	If in step 2 the user enters invalid/wrong information, display the error message "Invalid login" and exit\
2) No GPS connectivity\
	If the GPS module cannot be accessed to provide data in step 4, display message "check GPS module" and exit\
3) Garbled/incorrect GPS data\
	If the GPS module is malfunctioning in step 4, display message "check GPS module" and exit\
4) Invalid login location\
	If in step 5, the current GPS co-ordinates do not match with a valid location, display message "Please move to a secure / approved location before logging in" and exit\
5) Connection to Citrix servers fails\
	If in step 3, Citrix cannot be reached on the network, display "CITRIX server unreachable" and exit\
6) Connection to remote gps database fails\
	If in step 5, the database cannot be reached on the network, display "GPS server unreachable" and exit\
