\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\ql\qnatural

\b\fs28 \cf0  Basic Flow of Events\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs24 \cf0 1. Professor moves.\
2. The GPS module checks the professor's current location\
3. This GPS co-ordinate data is checked against a remote database of valid geolocations\
4. The system verifies that the co-ordinate is acceptable.\
5. The user remains logged into the system\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\ql\qnatural

\b\fs28 \cf0  Alternative Flows
\b0 \
1) User moves to insecure location\
	If in step 1, the user moves outside of his "safe" bounds, this is detected in step 3, and in step 4, the user is booted out of the system. A message is also displayed saying "please remain in a secure location."\
\
2) GPS module loses connection\
	If during normal use, the gps module becomes unreachable, they lose connectivity, and a message is displayed stating that the user must reconnect the module before continuing.}